{"parse":{"title":"Berkeley Digital Film Institute","pageid":19691749,"revid":827252976,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span id=\"coordinates\"><a href=\"/wiki/Geographic_coordinate_system\" title=\"Geographic coordinate system\">Coordinates</a>: <span class=\"plainlinks nourlexpansion\"><a class=\"external text\" href=\"//tools.wmflabs.org/geohack/geohack.php?pagename=Berkeley_Digital_Film_Institute&amp;params=37_51_30.5_N_122_17_25.84_W_region:US\"><span class=\"geo-default\"><span class=\"geo-dms\" title=\"Maps, aerial photos, and other data for this location\"><span class=\"latitude\">37\u00b051\u203230.5\u2033N</span> <span class=\"longitude\">122\u00b017\u203225.84\u2033W</span></span></span><span class=\"geo-multi-punct\">&#xfeff; / &#xfeff;</span><span class=\"geo-nondefault\"><span class=\"geo-dec\" title=\"Maps, aerial photos, and other data for this location\">37.858472\u00b0N 122.2905111\u00b0W</span><span style=\"display:none\">&#xfeff; / <span class=\"geo\">37.858472; -122.2905111</span></span></span></a></span></span></span>\n</p><p>The <b>Berkeley Digital Film Institute</b> is a <a href=\"/wiki/San_Francisco_Bay_Area\" title=\"San Francisco Bay Area\">San Francisco Bay Area</a> film school founded in early 2007 by Patrick Kriwanek, Dean of Education. The program is a 16-month program with emphasis on Producing and Directing for Motion Pictures, Television, Commercials and Music Videos.    Kriwanek, who was the head of the Academy of Art's Motion Picture division was instrumental in growing the program from 79 to 900 students before leaving in 1999.  <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a><